goal_descEN: Protect, restore and promote sustainable use of terrestrial ecosystems, sustainably manage forests, combat desertification, and halt and reverse land degradation and halt biodiversity loss
target_descEN: By 2020, ensure the conservation, restoration and sustainable use of terrestrial and inland freshwater ecosystems and their services, in particular forests, wetlands, mountains and drylands, in line with obligations under international agreements
indicator_descEN: Proportion of important sites for terrestrial and freshwater biodiversity that are covered by protected areas, by ecosystem type
series_tags: ['water', 'freshwater', 'biological diversity', 'freshwater ecosystems', 'natural resources', 'national parks and protected areas']
seriesDescription: Average proportion of Freshwater Key Biodiversity Areas (KBAs) covered by protected areas (%)
sources: BirdLife International, IUCN and UNEP-WCMC (2018). Based on spatial overlap between polygons for Key Biodiversity Areas from the World Database of key Biodiveristy Areas (www.keybiodiversityareas.org) and polygons for protected areas from the World Database on Protected Areas (www.protectedplanet.net)

goal_descEN: Protect, restore and promote sustainable use of terrestrial ecosystems, sustainably manage forests, combat desertification, and halt and reverse land degradation and halt biodiversity loss
target_descEN: By 2020, ensure the conservation, restoration and sustainable use of terrestrial and inland freshwater ecosystems and their services, in particular forests, wetlands, mountains and drylands, in line with obligations under international agreements
indicator_descEN: Proportion of important sites for terrestrial and freshwater biodiversity that are covered by protected areas, by ecosystem type
series_tags: ['water', 'freshwater', 'biological diversity', 'freshwater ecosystems', 'natural resources', 'national parks and protected areas']
seriesDescription: Average proportion of Freshwater Key Biodiversity Areas (KBAs) covered by protected areas (%)
